{"name": "Studies in Perception IV: Julie Martin", "description": "This portrait of Julie Martin, Director of Experiments in Art and Technology (E.A.T.), was created in 2022 by Ken Knowlton and Jim Boulton. It was made with a reconstruction of the algorithm Knowlton and Leon Harmon used to create the 1966 artwork Studies in Perception I, also known as Computer Nude. 

  Computer Nude was displayed at a press conference for E.A.T., held in October 1967 at Robert Rauschenbergb�s Lafayette Street studio.
